        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mrs-diana-organ' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0355P0_20001025_WH_78' title='Link to this speech by Mrs Diana Organ' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mrs-diana-organ" title="Mrs Diana Organ">Mrs. Organ</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I thank my right hon. Friend the Minister for her very clear answers, which provide some avenues for us to pursue, especially those relating to the Crown. In some areas, we now know that there are new
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_114wh' title='Col. 114WH &mdash; HC Deb 25 October 2000 vol 355 c114WH' name='column_114wh' href='#column_114wh' rel='bookmark'>114WH</a>
            arguments for us to marshal. We shall have to look at her answers and be aware that, in some cases, we are going to win and in others, we are not&#x2014;
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0355P0_20001025_WH_79'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mrs-ray-michie' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
